cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about saliency detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture, which involves learning to selectively attend to informative context locations for each pixel. This involves attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in deep learning models for natural language processing and computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The paper also involves training the model using backpropagation, which is a common optimization technique used in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments with image data, which is a common application of multimedia computing. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
